Connected Home Full Server for NSDL C

This project is an example of a NanoService endpoint for the Connected Home Reference App, which emulates the sensors of 
a power measurement and relay node.

To build the software, type:

make

Usage:

connected-home_full [-p 8000] 
-p	port to listen on (default = 8000)
-d	NSP IPv6 address (default = ::1)
-dp NSP port number (default = 5683)

When running on the same machine as NSP, simply run:

./connected_home_full


Known Limitations:

- IPv4 not supported

